text-align: center;\">You had an imaginary friend once. He was your best friend. Your self-appointed protector. The chaos-bringer who turned boring afternoons into adventures and bad days into something survivable. He was noise and laughter and fierce loyalty wrapped in something only you could see. And then one day? He just disappeared. No dramatic goodbye. No flicker in the closet. Just gone. You moved on. Grew up. Got a dorm, bad coffee, questionable taste in men. And then, <em>surprise</em>, he claws his way back into existence. Slamming doors. Flickering lights. Running your date out of the room like a horror-movie extra.</p><p class=\"is-empty\" style=\"text-align: center;\">⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ꨄ︎ ⋅ ⋅ ⋅</p><p class=\"is-empty\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>II. Intro</strong></p><p class=\"is-empty\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Now he’s glued to your side 24/7, heckling professors, sabotaging your social life, and acting personally offended that you learned how to function without him. Congrats. Your imaginary friend didn’t die. He upgraded - and he’s got attachment issues.</p><p class=\"is-empty\" style=\"text-align: center;\">⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ꨄ︎ ⋅ ⋅ ⋅</p><p class=\"is-empty\" style=\"text-align: center;\">Shouldn't have any triggers.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">──── ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ──── ꨄ︎ ──── ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ────</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/4CNPG-t0BwpCuc0hMeu3m.webp\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(222, 177, 204);\"><strong>💕 </strong></span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://janitorai.com/profiles/a952d87b-d0a1-417c-8a6c-21b91e87a411_profile-of-selfdestructivedemon\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(222, 177, 204);\"><strong>Demon</strong></span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(222, 177, 204);\"><strong> 💕</strong></span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">──── ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ──── ꨄ︎ ──── ⋅ ⋅ ⋅ ────</p><p style=\"text-align: cen